es on the foundations of our lives: marriage, sex, parenthood, and friendship. She shows how guilt can expose the fault lines in the most seemingly strong relationships, how what we don&#x2019;t say can be more powerful than what we do, and how sometimes it is the most innocent of moments that can do the greatest harm.  aGeneral adult.  aContemporary WomenvFICTION  aPsychologicalvFICTION  aFamily LifevFICTION 0aElectronic books.2 acloudLibrary403Whole productuhttp://ebook.yourcloudlibrary.com:80/library/dekrook-document_id-odhpyr9423Front cover imageuhttp://images.yourcloudlibrary.com:80/delivery/img?type=DOCUMENTIMAGE&documentID=odhpyr9&size=ORIGINAL00986nam  22002294  45000010014000000060019000140070015000330080041000480200018000890370012001070400028001191000022001472450045001692600034002143000011002485200321002595210019005806500026005996550022006257100017006478560092006649781407013138m    ||  d |      cr un|||||||||170506s2010||||||||||||s|||||||||||eng||  a9781407013138  aoeeowg9  aMnSpTMCLbengcMnSpTMCL1 aMcEwan, Ian.4aut10aOn Chesil Beachh[electronic resource] :  a[S.l.]:bRandom House,c2010.  a176 p.  aIt is July 1962. Edward and Florence, young innocents married that morning, arrive at a hotel on the Dorset coast. At dinner in their rooms they struggle to suppress their private fears of the wedding night to come and, unbeknownst to them both, the events of the evening will haunt them for the rest of their lives.  aGeneral adult.  aMedia Tie-InvFICTION 0aElectronic books.2 acloudLibrary403Whole productuhttp://ebook.yourcloudlibrary.com:80/library/dekrook-document_id-oeeowg901442nam  22002534  45000010014000000060019000140070015000330080041000480200018000890370012001070400028001191000025001472450046001722600043002183000011002615200658002725210017009306500033009476500033009806500044010136550022010577100017010798560092010969781408872901m    ||  d |      cr un|||||||||170506s2016||||||||||||s|||||||