hips that will help America win the war. One evening at a nightclub, she meets Dexter Styles again, and begins to understand the complexity of her father&#x2019;s life, the reasons he might have vanished. With the atmosphere of a noir thriller, Egan&#x2019;s first historical novel follows Anna and Styles into a world populated by gangsters, sailors, divers, bankers, and union men. Manhattan Beach is a deft, dazzling, propulsive exploration of a transformative moment in the lives and identities of women and men, of America and the world. It is a magnificent novel by the author of A Visit from the Goon Squad, one of the great writers of our time.  aLiteraryvFICTION  aHistoricalvFICTION 0aElectronic books.2 acloudLibrary403Whole productuhttps://ebook.yourcloudlibrary.com/library/dekrook-document_id-o2bdcz9423Front cover imageuhttps://images.yourcloudlibrary.com/delivery/img?type=DOCUMENTIMAGE&documentID=o2bdcz9&size=ORIGINAL01818nam  22002534  45000010014000000060019000140070015000330080041000480200018000890370026001070400028001331000027001612450075001882600034002633000011002975201025003085210019013336500033013526500027013856500023014126550022014357100017014578560090014749781473520370m    ||  d |      cr un|||||||||171020s2017||||||||||||s|||||||||||eng||  a9781473520370  apguf4r9bcloudLibrary  aMnSpTMCLbengcMnSpTMCL1 aChevalier, Tracy.4aut10aNew BoybOthello Retold (Hogarth Shakespeare)h[electronic resource] :  a[S.l.]:bRandom House,c2017.  a192 p.  a'O felt her presence behind him like a fire at his back.' Arriving at his fourth school in six years, diplomat&#x2019;s son Osei Kokote knows he needs an ally if he is to survive his first day &#x2013; so he&#x2019;s lucky to hit it off with Dee, the most popular girl in school. But one student can&#x2019;t stand to witness this budding relationship: Ian decides to destroy the friendship between the black boy and the golden girl. By the end of the day, the school and its key players &#x2013; teachers and pupils alike &#x2013; will never be the same again. The tragedy of Othello is transposed to a 1970s&#x2019; suburban Washington schoolyard, where kids fall in and out of love with each other before lunchtime, and practise a casual racism picked up from their parents and teachers. Watching over the shoulders of four 11-year-olds &#x2013; Osei, Dee, Ian and his reluctant girlfriend Mimi &#x2013; Tracy Chevalier's powerful drama of friends torn apart by jealousy, bullying and betrayal will leave you reeling.  aGeneral adult.  aHistoricalvAfrican American  aComing of AgevFICTION  aShakespearevDRAMA 0aElectronic books.2 acloudLibrary403Whole productuhttps://ebook.yourcloudlibrary.com/library/dekrook-document_id-pguf4r901861nam  22002774  45000010014000000060019000140070015000330080041000480200018000890370026001070400028001331000024001612450082001852600039002673000011003065200964003175210019012816500043013006500039013436500019013826500029014016500024014306550022014547100017014768560090014939781405933810m    ||  d |      cr un|||||||||171020s2017||||||||||||s|||||||||||eng||  a9781405933810  apkhgo89bcloudLibrary  aMnSpTMCLbengcMnSpTMCL1 aFrench, Nicci.4aut10aSunday Morning Coming DownbA Frieda Klein Novel (7)h[electronic resource] :  a[S.l.]:bPenguin Books Ltd,c2017.  a320 p.  aGOOD HOUSEKEEPING'S BOOK OF THE MONTH . . . 'Nicci French's sophisticated, compassionate and gripping crime novels stand head and shoulders above the competition' Sophie Hannah It's always darkest before the light comes. In the penultimate, chilling seventh instalment of the bestselling, critically acclaimed Frieda Klein series, evil looms but this time it's far too close to home . . . 'There's a body in Saffron Mews . . .' __________ Psychotherapist Frieda Klein's home is her refuge until she returns to find it has become a disturbingly bloody crime scene. Beneath the floorboards the police have found the body of a man she